headline: Data-Provider Stocks Tumble on AI Competition Fears
summary: Financial data-provider stocks dropped after artificial-intelligence company Anthropic announced it added new functions for legal users of its Cowork assistant. While shares of European legal publishers were the first to drop, the selloff quickly expanded to market-data heavyweights.

headline: Wall Street Left Bereft After ‘High Priest’ of S&P 500 Retires
summary: Silverblatt, longtime senior index analyst, retired after nearly 49 years at S&P Global.  Known for his encyclopedic knowledge of markets, his other titles include the high priest of the S&P 500 index, the dean of data and the earnings pope.

headline: S&P Global Introduces New Brand Identity for Mobility Division as "Mobility Global"
summary: S&P Global (NYSE: SPGI) today announced Mobility Global, Inc ("Mobility Global") will be the corporate name for the S&P Global Mobility business upon completion of its planned separation from S&P Global into a standalone public company. The Mobility Global name reflects its leadership in providing critical intelligence across the vehicle lifecycle to suppliers, OEMs, dealers, and consumers worldwide.
